description.narrative:
Activities include:

1) Train community-owned resource persons to mobilize, educate, and provide referrals; 

2) Mobilize target groups for increased awareness and demand for services; 

3) Develop and deliver a project-level targeted information, education, and communication (IEC)/behavior change communication (BCC) approach and materials; 

5) Increase service points for condom access; 

6) Conduct community dialogues; 

7) Involve district structures to support environmental change; 

8) Build capacity and support district coordination structures; 

9) Develop and implement systems for project-level capacity building and coordination; 

10) Ensure referral and follow up of target population; 

11) Conduct situational analysis to inform project approaches; 

12) Implement project-level Monitoring and Evaluation
